description:
PREWAR CONDO - VIEWS - LOCATION - PERFECTION!

This HUUUGE 1 bedroom CONDO, has over 9’ CEILINGS and herringbone OAK FLOORS.
*LOW MONTHLY COSTS* makes this perfect for INVESTORS and savvy homeowners.
CLOSETS GALORE and outfitted! 
Washer / Dryers ALLOWED in unit!
Windowed EAT-IN KITCHEN, Stainless Steel Appliances and Granite countertops.
SOUTHERN & NORTHERN VIEWS, the apartment is flooded with SUNLIGHT all day. Breathtaking VIEWS of the city.
RENOVATED BATHROOM with deep SOAKING TUB / Shower, chrome fixtures and large vanity / sink.

This is a special building that offers all the scale and proportion of PREWAR architecture and all the amenities of a CONDO.

165 West 91st Street has been meticulously restored as evidenced by the magnificent marble lobby. The FULL SERVICE condo includes a 24-hour doorman and live-in resident manager. INVESTOR FRIENDLY, one can rent out in perpetuity!
PETS WELCOME!

AMENITIES: landscaped GORGEOUS ROOF DECK, FITNESS room, playroom, and BIKE room. LAUNDRY room in basement.
Located in the heart of the Upper West Side, convenient to CENTRAL PARK, Riverside Park, shopping, restaurants, and mass transportation.
NO ASSESSMENTS - healthy financials
10% Down / 90% Financing allowed
NO FLIP TAX
PRICED TO SELL! Don’t miss out on this opportunity!

Currently there is a tenant in place until December paying $3,950 but it CAN BE DELIVERED VACANT.
